{
  "enabled": false,
  "name": "init-database-model",
  "description": "Initialize SQLAlchemy model structure for new database models",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileCreated",
    "patterns": [
      "backend/app/models/**/*.py"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A new database model file has been created at ${FILE}. Please use Desktop Commander MCP to add the standard SQLAlchemy model structure:\n\n```python\n\"\"\"\n[Model name] database model\n\nThis module defines the [model name] table structure.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom sqlalchemy import Column, Integer, String, DateTime, ForeignKey, Boolean, Text\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import relationship\nfrom sqlalchemy.sql import func\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nfrom ..core.database import Base\n\nclass [ModelName](Base):\n    \"\"\"[Model description]\"\"\"\n    \n    __tablename__ = \"[table_name]\"\n    \n    # Primary key\n    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True, index=True)\n    \n    # Timestamps\n    created_at = Column(DateTime, default=func.now(), nullable=False)\n    updated_at = Column(DateTime, default=func.now(), onupdate=func.now(), nullable=False)\n    \n    # User association (if applicable)\n    user_id = Column(Integer, ForeignKey(\"users.id\"), nullable=False, index=True)\n    \n    # Add your fields here\n    # name = Column(String(255), nullable=False)\n    # description = Column(Text, nullable=True)\n    # is_active = Column(Boolean, default=True, nullable=False)\n    \n    # Relationships\n    # user = relationship(\"User\", back_populates=\"[table_name]\")\n    \n    def __repr__(self):\n        return f\"<[ModelName](id={self.id})>\"\n```\n\nUse mcp_desktop_commander_mcp_write_file() to write the template. Replace [placeholders] with appropriate names based on the filename. Skip if the file is not in the models directory or is __init__.py."
  },
  "blocking": false
}